This paper discusses the manipulation of bibliometric indicators offered by Google Scholar Citations and Google Scholar Metrics. It involves creating false documents and citing them to increase the H index of authors and journals. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
